First implementation on SSR. LFAP Protocol version 3.

ctLFAP.description: This mib module defines an SNMP enterprise MIB under Cabletron Enterprise. RFC 2124. Light-weight Flow Admission Protocol.

flowPolicyControl.name: flowPolicyControl
flowPolicyControl.description: This object allows flow policy to be enabled or disabled on each switch. Setting this object to disable(1) disables flow policy functionality on the switch. Setting this object to enable(2) enables the flow policy function.

flowPolicyStatus.name: flowPolicyStatus
flowPolicyStatus.description: This object gives the status of flow policy processing on each switch. The value of disabled(1) indicates that the flow policy function has been totally disabled. The value of enabled(2) indicates that the flow policy functions have been enabled and is searching for a policy server. The value of active(3) indicates that the flow policy function is fully operational. The value of error(4) indicates that the flow policy function has experienced some fatal error and has disabled itself.

flowPolicyActiveServer.name: flowPolicyActiveServer
flowPolicyActiveServer.description: This object reflects the IP address of the remote policy server currently being used.

flowPolicyServerAddrTable.name: flowPolicyServerAddrTable
flowPolicyServerAddrTable.description: An ordered list of flow policy server addresses with which flow policy processing will attempt to establish contact.

flowPolicyServerAddrEntry.name: flowPolicyServerAddrEntry
flowPolicyServerAddrEntry.description: A component entry containing objects for a particular server.

flowPolicyServerAddrIndex.name: flowPolicyServerAddrIndex
flowPolicyServerAddrIndex.description: A unique value for each flow policy server address that indexes the table.

flowPolicyServerAddr.name: flowPolicyServerAddr
flowPolicyServerAddr.description: This object contains the address of a flow policy server.

flowPolicyConfigPolicy.name: flowPolicyConfigPolicy
flowPolicyConfigPolicy.description: This object indicates whether or not the CCE supports connection policy. A value of available(1) indicates that connection policy support is available from this CCE. A value of unavailable(2) indicates that this CCE is incapable of supporting connection policy.

flowPolicyConfigStatistics.name: flowPolicyConfigStatistics
flowPolicyConfigStatistics.description: This object indicates whether or not the CCE supports connection statistics. A value of available(1) indicates that connection statistics are supported from this CCE. A value of unavailable(2) indicates that this CCE is incapable of supporting connection statistics.

flowPolicyPollingTimerInterval.name: flowPolicyPollingTimerInterval
flowPolicyPollingTimerInterval.description: This object contains the number of minutes between statistics polling periods.

flowPolicyPollingBatchSize.name: flowPolicyPollingBatchSize
flowPolicyPollingBatchSize.description: This object specifies the number of connections that comprise a batch for polling purposes.

flowPolicyPollingBatchInterval.name: flowPolicyPollingBatchInterval
flowPolicyPollingBatchInterval.description: This object contains the current number of milliseconds between statistics polling batches. A polling period is divided into polling batches, the duration between which is calculated by dividing the value of flowPolicyPollingTimerInterval times 60,000 by the number of batches. The number of polling batches is calculated by dividing the actual number of connections by the value of flowPolicyPollingBatchSize. Between batches, the statistics polling mechanism pauses this number of milliseconds.

flowPolicyPollingBatchUpdateInterval.name: flowPolicyPollingBatchUpdateInterval
flowPolicyPollingBatchUpdateInterval.description: This object specifies the time in seconds to send flow create and delete information to the server.

flowPolicyPollingLostContactInterval.name: flowPolicyPollingLostContactInterval
flowPolicyPollingLostContactInterval.description: This object specifies the time to wait in seconds until the CCE realizes it has lost contact with a server.

flowPolicyPollingServerRetryInterval.name: flowPolicyPollingServerRetryInterval
flowPolicyPollingServerRetryInterval.description: This object specifies the time in seconds to wait before trying to connect to the server(s) in the list after being unable to connect to any of the server(s).

flowPolicyPollingSendQueueMaxSize.name: flowPolicyPollingSendQueueMaxSize
flowPolicyPollingSendQueueMaxSize.description: This object specifies the maximum number of messages the send queue can hold before messages are dropped.

flowPolicyPollingTaskPriority.name: flowPolicyPollingTaskPriority
